at|mitche: Play:  South led the @DAce.
What other card does North know is in the South hand besides the @DAce that she just saw at trick 1? The @DKing.
But even if South pulled the @dAce out by mistake, North should play the @DQueen, not the @d10.
Why?  Here, it says I guarantee the @dJack -- 100%! 
If South needs a card to be led thru declarer she could lead a (higher or lower) @D to the known J
To say "please shift to the (higher or lower) side suit.
"A high spot asks for a spade return, a low spot for a club".
