nt||at|mitche:  Another defensive tip.  Other things being equal, try not to lead dummy's long suit 
(there are exceptions, of course, as when you think pard can ruff one of declarer's winners).
On a spade return by North, declarer cannot avoid going down 2.
As it is, declarer should take care to unblock the clubs to arrange for a spade discard.

